annotation.TEXT: Hmm... I don't know if I want to go to an arena yet, so let's just explore some more.
Aw, no music change? I was totally expecting "Pushing Onwards" to begin playing here.
No duders in the trenches here (nor is there a trinket).
Oh, yeah. Gotta make every vanishing platform disappear at least once!
Yeah, this passage is now blocked off.
I wonder if this means that the six rooms below are used for something else in this player level...
Alright, I'm back... Ow.
It kinda feels weird playing through SS1 backwards.
Oh, man. Music change. Hmm... I'm smart, right?
Whoa, this is different... Umm...
Alright, I think now's a good time to try warping to "T4".

Huh, this moving platform here doesn't even work. I think I read somewhere that the two instances in the main game of a moving platform having to be freed from a vanishing platform are hard coded to do that, and you can't do a setup like that in the level editor, because it won't work right.
Okay, here's the other side of that blocked off passage. I wonder why it was blocked off like that.
15 deaths today. Not bad. I think the Imperfect Crush Device killed me more than any other single room so far, and even that wasn't too terrible.
Hello, and welcome back to Back to VVVVVV!
Yeah, this whole area seems to have absolutely no enemy sprites either.
Oh, man! We're getting close to Veni Vidi Vici now!
That trinket has already been obtained, story-wise, of course.
Hmm... What could be this way, down this spike-filled corridor? A trinket, perhaps?
Ooh, shiny! And a "T4" terminal! Okay, those are definitely new!
The trinket that used to be on the left side of "You Just Keep Coming Back" is no longer there. (Again, likely because Viridian already got it, story-wise.)
Let me go back to those rooms that used to have "LIES" going through them...
Ah, yes. The "doomS" and "Swoop" rooms.
Cool, it worked, even though I hadn't accessed "T4" from this side yet. Does that mean I can use any of the warps from the sort-of hub as I please?
Huh, looks like there's been some modifications to this place, with new openings here and there.
...Oh, brother. Okay, this made me laugh.
So, next time, I'll try to get past those hypnotic hearts, and explore the rest of this place where only smart people belong. To be continued... Yo!
Alright, let's fill out a few more rooms on the map up here, and then continue onwards with SS2.

Well, I'm back to where I began the main game, but there's no teleporter here, and I didn't see any new openings along the way that I could use to shortcut out of here, so let me work my way back to "Driller" at ludicrous speed!
Huh... How do I reach that area to the left where that poison cloud machine used to be?

Ah, yes. This "Gordian Knot" room, which was my biggest obstacle when I was trying to V-rank Space Station 2 in the Time Trials. Fortunately, I don't have to bother with the underside of it this time!
So, let's finish off the SS2 exploration now.
Yeah, no bus here. I want to say that the bus is the biggest enemy sprite in VVVVVV, but if I'm wrong, let me know.
Yes, made it! ...Whoa...
Huh, no enemies on the bottom half of "Backsliders", but IIRC, the enemies that were here were those garbage blocks, which I know are definitely usable in player levels...
And, of course, no bouncing stop signs.
No trinket here, likely because, story-wise, Viridian already has this trinket.
Once again, no bus.
Yep!
Ow, I need to be further to the right.
This room looks like it works exactly like it did before. (One Of A Nice Kind pointed out that the checkpoint on the right is a little bit off compared to its main game position.)
Fortunately, with no "LIES" coming through here, this place is a piece of cake.
This room is playing "Positive Force", which normally plays in The Tower. I wonder if this room is related to The Tower in some way? Well, we'll probably find out in the future.
I remember when "Give Me A V" used to give me trouble for some reason, but now I can handle it easily.
Ow, why'd I flip there? (LOL, I managed to die once here anyway, despite this place being disabled!)
No weird walking things or ghosts around here.
Okay, the path to the shiny is rather obvious. I just have to be careful.
Huh, no enemies on the lower half of "You Chose... Poorly".
Ow, my Strawmander!
Of course, not everyone experiences Google's glitches. It often seems like I'm the only one that has issues with some of the glitches.
Those hearts are like... hypnotic or something...
Ow, my Squirpie!
Am I going to take control of Vitellary now, just like how I controlled Valso during a part of Dimension Open? That'd be neat.
I wonder if this is one of Koishi's mind... games... mind... games...
Well, since the "TRUTH"s were gone, it only makes sense that the "LIES" are gone as well.
Yep.
This room looks unchanged, although I'm not expecting to see a tutorial message mentioning that I can use the up and down arrows to flip here.
Yeah, those teleporters don't know how to accurately measure smartness!
No coins to dodge here, which I have seen plenty of in other player levels. I wonder why there are no enemy sprites in this place at all...
The game just automatically made me move to the left into these teleporters after that conversation ended.
This room's name is changed to something entirely new. Also, we're going with the version of the room with the row of spikes removed, apparently.
Hey there, Vitellary! Yeah, I hate spikes too.
I wonder why "Down Under" was changed to have conveyors instead of its usual moving platforms?
There's a new gap in the ceiling of "Plain Sailing from Here On", which is convenient.
Looks like we've got terminals all going from "T0" to "TF" without any gaps in the hexadecimal numbering, unlike in Dimension Open.
So, I can't reach that area that used to have the poison clouds from here. But, maybe I can just warp there from the sort-of hub, since there was a "T4" terminal...
I guess not. Well, that search for the switch didn't take long.
Gotcha! I now have 5% of the trinkets in this level!
No terminal or weird stationary object that kills Viridian on contact here. Also, more new openings.
Alright, I think I'm done exploring Space Station 2. Let's take a look around the sort-of hub now.
Okay, the passages I can take from here are different. I've been trying to play through SS2 the normal way for the most part, but it looks like I'll have to deviate from that plan here.
I do recall having been to the "TB" terminal before, so why don't I head back there? ..."East Of Arena", eh?
...If I can avoid stubbing my toe in "Sorrow".
And, we're back to "Passion for Exploring". Alright, so I can't really accomplish anything from "T4", so I'm going to return to "T5" and go backwards through SS1.
So, last time, I went through a lengthy prologue and then filled out a good chunk of the map.
Yeah, I figured that wasn't a wraparound screen, because otherwise, how would I escape besides dying?
Ah, there's a "T5" terminal, so the large circular teleporter that was here was replaced with a terminal teleporter, I take it.
There's new openings here, too. These new openings may end up coming in handy if I need to quickly make my way through this place again later.
Alright, so let's check out Space Station 2!
No "TRUTH"s to dodge here. Well, I don't know if the level editor can allow for special enemy sprites like those.
No deadly disc going up and down here.
Okay, so what does the area to the left of "Driller" look like?

And, I guess I'm stuck in here now. Well, I guess I have to finish this place now. It's been over ten minutes so far, but I think I'll play just a little longer, since a lot of this time was me basically exploring old areas from the main game.
I agree. It's definitely faulty. I bet Google got ahold of it and broke something within it.
